LIM

PURPOSE
     Check numeric telemetry in CI.

     Programs emit key=value lines. lim checks them against rules, emits JSONL
     events, and exits nonzero when an error rule trips.

CLI
     cc -std=c99 -Wall -Wextra -O2 lim.c -o lim
     ./my_test_or_benchmark | ./lim -r .lim/rules.lim

GITHUB ACTION
     - uses: njlane314/lim@v1
       with:
         rules: .lim/rules.lim
         command: ./my_test_or_benchmark

RULES
     Format:

         key op number level event_id

     Example:

         frame.ms              > 16.6    warn   frame.slow
         queue.depth           > 1000    error  queue.backpressure
         tokens.per_second     < 50      error  inference.too_slow

     Operators:

         > >= < <= == !=

     Levels:

         info warn error

INPUT
     Accepted forms:

         frame.ms=18.7
         queue.depth 1402

OUTPUT
     JSONL events on stdout:

         {"ts":1760000000,"level":"warn","id":"frame.slow","key":"frame.ms","op":">","threshold":16.600000000000001,"value":18.699999999999999}

     Exit status:

         0  no failing rule
         1  failing warn/error rule, depending on --fail-on
         2  invalid input, rule, or argument

BUILD
     make
     make test

EXAMPLES
     examples/github-actions/       reusable action workflow example
     examples/deployments/          llama, zstd, and PX4-style adapters

     Run them:

         examples/github-actions/test-project.sh
         examples/deployments/test-all.sh

EMBEDDING
     Compile with -DLIM_NO_MAIN and include lim.h from a C or C++ test harness.

         cc -std=c99 -Wall -Wextra -O2 -DLIM_NO_MAIN example.c lim.c -o example

LICENSE
     MIT.
